   > # end of Font
   <String `General insurance rules : '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 1459443>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `The concept behind r. 2(2) of the General Insurance Business '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `(Nationalisation) Rules, 1973, is to permit the insurance corporation to enter the amount of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `reserve in the profit and loss account in the expenditure side which would not have been per'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `missible otherwise because the amount set apart in a reserve cannot be expenditure. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `rule puts a stamp of permissibility on something not permissible otherwise. This rule itself is '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `suggestive of the fact that the amount set apart in a reserve is not expenditure in its commer'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `cial sense. The General Insurance Business Rules do not go beyond providing an accounting '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `method. They cannot be pressed into service for altering the basic character of an amount '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `which is not an expenditure. Merely because r. 2(2)(a) permits the amount set apart for '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `redemption of preference shares being debited to the profit and loss account, the amount so '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `set apart does not become an amount of expenditure for all intents and purposes so as to fall '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `within the meaning of “expenditure” as employed in r. 5(a) and cannot be added back : '>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 1459447>
    <ETag `Caseref'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Caselaw'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `Gene'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
