    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `Tax Recovery Officer has no power to declare transfer pending tax proceedings '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `void : '>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 1460326>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `The powers of the TRO are different from what section 281 declares. Under r. 11, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Schedule II, where any claim is preferred to, or any objection is made to the attachment or '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `sale of, any property in execution of a certificate on the ground that such property is not liable '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `to attachment or sale, the TRO shall proceed to investigate the claim or objection. The TRO '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `has to examine who is in possession of the property and in what capacity. He can only attach '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 70>
   <String `property in the possession of the assessee in his own right, or in the possession of a tenant '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `or a third party on behalf of or for the benefit of the assessee. He cannot declare any transfer '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `made by the assessee in favour of a third party void. If the Department finds that a property of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the assessee is transferred by him to a third party with intention to defraud the Revenue, it '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `will have to file a suit under r. 11(6) to have the transfer declared void under s. 281 : '>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 1460329>
    <ETag `Caseref'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <ElementReferenced Yes>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Caselaw'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `TRO v. '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Gangadhra Viswanath Ranade (decd. through lr) [1998] 234 ITR 188'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `Caseref'>
   <String `.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
   <ElementEnd `Notes'>
