    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `Contributions to employees’ welfare funds such as provident fund and employees’ '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `state insurance :'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `Title'>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 71286122>
    <ETag `Para'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String ` Amounts not earned by the assessee, but received by it, whether in the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `form of deductions, or otherwise, as receipts, to be treated as income, i. e., amounts received '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `(or deducted from employees) are part of the employer-assessee’s income. Since these '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `amounts are not receipts that belong to the assessee, but are held by it, as trustee, as it '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `were, section 36(1)(va) was inserted specifically to ensure that if these receipts are deposited '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `in the employees\q provident fund and employees’ State insurance accounts of the employees '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `concerned, they could be treated as deductions. Section 36(1)(va) is hedged with the condi'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `tion that the receipts have to be deposited by the employer, with the Employees\xd5 Provident '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Fund and Employees State Insurance, on or before the due date, that is the date by which '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `such amounts have to be credited by the employer, in the concerned enactments such as the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Employees’ Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 and the Employees’ '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `State Insurance Act, 1948. Such a condition (i. e., depositing the amount on or before the due '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `date) has not been enacted in relation to the employer’s contribution (i. e., section 36(1)(iv)).  '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `When Parliament introduced the amendments in 1988-89, inserting section 36(1)(va) and '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `simultaneously the second proviso to section 43B, its intention was not to treat the disparate '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `nature of the amounts, similarly. Section 2(24)(x) too, deems the amount received from the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `employees (whether from the employee or by way of deduction authorised by the statute) as '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `income – it is the character of the amount that is important, i. e., not income earned. The '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 101>
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `distinction between an employer’s contribution which is its primary liability under law – in '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `terms of section 36(1)(iv), and its liability to deposit amounts received by it or deducted by it '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `(section 36(1)(va)) is crucial. The former forms part of the employer’s income, and the latter '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `retains its character as an income (albeit deemed), by virtue of section 2(24)(x) – unless the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `conditions spelt out by the '>
   <ElementBegin 
    <Unique 71286125>
    <ETag `Emphasis'>
    <Attributes 
    > # end of Attributes
    <Collapsed No>
    <SpecialCase No>
    <AttributeDisplay AllAttributes>
   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `Emphasis'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String `Explanation'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `Emphasis'>
   <String ` to section 36(1)(va) are satisfied, i. e., depositing such '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `amount received or deducted from the employee on or before the due date. Thus, it is an '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `essential condition for the deduction that such amounts are deposited on or before the due '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `date : '>
