   > # end of ElementBegin
   <String `By Circular No. 693, dated November 17, 1994 (benefit of section '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `80HHC for export of processed minerals), the Central Board has clari'>
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `fied that the entry in the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `Twelfth Schedule is very clear and unambiguous and, therefore, for availing of the benefit '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `under section 80HHC, it is necessary that the rock is not only cut into blocks but also polished '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `before it is exported. This is in line with Government’s policy to encourage export of polished '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `granite and other rocks where value addition before export is high and to discourage export '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `of raw blocks where value addition is low : 211 ITR (St.) 25.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
