   <String `By Circular No. 729, dated November 1, 1995, the Central Board clari'>
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `fied its earlier Circu'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `lar No. 693, dated November 17, 1994, that while granite can alone be considered as min'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <TextRectID 129>
   <String `eral, any process applied to granite would deprive the quality of rough mineral from the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `dimensional blocks of granite, which is a value added marketable commodity. When rough '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `granite is cut to dimensional blocks of uniform colour and size, it not only undergoes mechan'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ical process of cutting, but also, a certain amount of dressing and polishing is involved to '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `remove '>
   <Char DiscHyphen>
   <String `various natural flaws such as colour variations, grain variations, joints fissures, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `moles, patches, hair line cracks, etc. Therefore, the profits derived from the export of such '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `granite dimensional blocks would be eligible for deduction under section 80HHC : 216 ITR '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `(St.) 141.'>
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
   <ElementEnd `Notes'>
   <ElementEnd `Schedule'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
