    <FSeparation 4>
    <FColor `Blue'>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` By the Finance Act, 2007, rule 60 which provides for application to set aside sale of immovable '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `property on deposit of the amount specified in the proclamation of sale for the recovery of which the sale was ordered, '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `with interest on such amount at the rate of fifteen per cent. per annum, calculated from the date of the proclamation of '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `sale to the date when deposit is made, was amended by substitution of the words “one and one-fourth per cent. for '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `every month or part of a month” for the words “fifteen per cent. per annum” in clause (a) of sub-rule (1), so as to provide '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `that the interest shall be chargeable at the rate of one and one-fourth per cent. for every month or part of a month '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `instead of fifteen per cent. per annum.'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
   <ElementEnd `Notes'>
   <Marker 
    <MType 10>
