   > # end of ElementBegin
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <String ` The proviso to sub-rule (1) of rule 3 of the Fourth Schedule under which where recognition has '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `been accorded to any provident fund on or before March 31, 2006, and such provident fund does not satisfy the condi'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `tions set out in clause (ea) of rule 4, and any other conditions which the Board may, by rules specify in this behalf, the '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `recognition to such fund shall be withdrawn, if such fund does not satisfy such conditions on or before March 31, 2007 '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `was amended by substitution of the words “31st day of March, 2007” for the words “31st day of March, 2008” to extend '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `the said time limit for compliance with the conditions by one more year, i.e., up to March 31, 2008. [This time was fur'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `ther extended up to March 31, 2009 by the Finance Act, 2008.] A proviso to sub-rule (1) was also inserted so as to pro'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `vide that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply to the provident fund of an establishment in respect of which '>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `a notification has been issued by the Central Government under sub-section (2) of section 16 of the Employees’ Provi'>
   <Char SoftHyphen>
  > # end of ParaLine
  <ParaLine 
   <String `dent Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952.'>
   <Font 
    <FTag `'>
    <FDW  -1.0%>
    <FLocked No>
   > # end of Font
   <ElementEnd `Para'>
  > # end of ParaLine
 > # end of Para
